-- Gulf Cement Reports Second-Quarter Loss of $5 Million as Prices Decline
-- Ayesha Daya
-- 2010-07-19T04:43:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/gulf-cement-reports-second-quarter-loss-of-5-million-as-prices-decline.html

          
          
             Gulf Cement Co., a United Arab
Emirates-based cement producer, reported a second-quarter loss
of 19.6 million dirhams as prices declined.  
 The company made a profit of 82 million dirhams in the
year-earlier period, according to a statement posted on the
website of the Abu Dhabi bourse today.  
